Child psychologist Catherine Deane (Jennifer Lopez) is an expert in an experimental
treatment for coma patients: a virtual reality device that allows her to enter into
the minds of her patients and attempt to coax them into consciousness. When serial
killer Carl Rudolph Stargher (Vincent D'Onofrio) falls into a coma before the FBI
can locate his final victim, Agent Peter Novak (Vince Vaughn) persuades Deane to
enter Stargher's mind and discover the victim's location.[1] Stargher's victim is
imprisoned in a cell in the form of a glass enclosure that is slowly filling with
water by means of an automatic timer.

Deane enters Stargher's twisted mind, where she is confronted by both the violent
and the innocent parts of the killer's psyche. The innocent half shows her the abuse
he suffered at his father's hands and the birth of his pathology when he drowned an
injured bird as a mercy killing. Deane attempts to nurture the innocent side of
Stargher's mind, but his murderous half thwarts her at every turn
